OL,3,CConsumer confidence falls again amid
OL,4,C'despondent mood' ahead of October
OL,5,CBudget
OL,7,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,8,Fretail and leisure for KPMG, said:
OL,9,F"Consumer confidence continues to be
OL,10,Finfluenced by three things: essential
OL,11,Fcosts for households, job security in
OL,12,Fa toughening labour market, and
OL,13,Fperception about the economic climate
OL,14,Fon the horizon."
OL,16,FMs Ellett said KPMG's own research
OL,17,Fshowed that people aged 65 and over
OL,18,Fare most likely to expect their
OL,19,Ffinancial security to worsen in the
OL,20,Fnext six months.
